## Auth Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User Browser
    participant FA as Firebase Auth
    participant API as API Route
    participant AM as Auth Middleware
    participant FS as Firestore

    U->>FA: signInWithEmailAndPassword / signInWithPopup(Google)
    FA-->>U: Firebase User + ID Token
    U->>API: authenticatedFetch (Bearer token in header)
    API->>AM: verifyAuthToken(request)
    AM->>FA: adminAuth.verifyIdToken(token)
    FA-->>AM: DecodedIdToken {uid, email}
    AM-->>API: AuthenticatedUser | 401
    API->>FS: Operations using authenticated UID
```

**Key observations:**
- All API routes use `requireAuth()` → server-side Firebase ID token verification
- Admin routes use `requireAdmin()` → checks `email === "aman.infratechai@gmail.com"` (hardcoded)
- Client uses `authenticatedFetch()` wrapper to auto-attach Bearer token
- No custom JWT — relies entirely on Firebase's token lifecycle
- No session cookies — stateless token auth on every request

