## Likely Risk Areas (Ranked)

### 🔴 CRITICAL

| # | Risk Area | Description |
|---|-----------|-------------|
| 1 | **Admin Panel — Client-Side Privilege** | Admin reads ALL user docs & writes subscription fields via client Firestore SDK. Firestore rules for `users` only allow reading own doc, meaning the admin panel likely fails silently OR the rules are more permissive than documented. Either way, any user who modifies frontend code to read all docs is a critical risk. |
| 2 | **Exposed Service Account Key** | `.env.local` contains the **full Firebase service account private key** (base64-encoded). This file is committed to the repo or at minimum sits unencrypted on disk. If leaked, an attacker has **full admin access** to the entire Firebase project. |
| 3 | **Client-Side Feature Gating** | `usePremium` hook gates AI tutor, custom exams, and repository access purely on the frontend. API routes do NOT enforce subscription tier. A free user can call `/api/ai/tutor` or `/api/exam/custom` unlimited times (within rate limits). |

### 🟠 HIGH

| # | Risk Area | Description |
|---|-----------|-------------|
| 4 | **Rate Limiter is Ephemeral** | In-memory `Map<string, RateLimitEntry>` resets on every Vercel cold start. Attackers can bypass by waiting for function recycling (~5 min idle). |
| 5 | **check-user-status: Unbounded Razorpay Enumeration** | Iterates up to 500 subscriptions + 500 payments on every call. At scale, this becomes an O(n) billing check that's expensive and slow. |
| 6 | **Admin Email Hardcoded** | `ADMIN_EMAIL = "aman.infratechai@gmail.com"` in source code. If this account is compromised, there's no MFA enforcement or rotation mechanism. |
| 7 | **No Subscription Expiry Enforcement** | Weekly Pass has no expiry date check. Once `weeklyPassUsed` is set and subscription is "active", the user stays Pro forever — no TTL or cron job to downgrade. |

### 🟡 MEDIUM

| # | Risk Area | Description |
|---|-----------|-------------|
| 8 | **AI Token Budget — Platform-wide, Not Per-User** | Daily limits (25k input / 75k output) are shared across ALL users. One power user can exhaust the entire day's budget. |
| 9 | **Path Traversal in Exam Routes** | `chapterId` parameter is used directly in `path.join(rawDir, ${chapterId}.xml)` — potential for `../../etc/passwd` style attacks. |
| 10 | **No CORS Configuration** | No explicit CORS headers — relies on Next.js defaults. External sites could make cross-origin requests. |
| 11 | **XML Parsing DoS** | `fast-xml-parser` processes user-influenced file content. Billion-laughs or entity expansion attacks possible if XML files are ever user-uploadable. |
| 12 | **Promo Code Enumeration** | Any authenticated user can read all promo codes. Attacker can enumerate valid referral codes. |

### 🟢 LOW

| # | Risk Area | Description |
|---|-----------|-------------|
| 13 | **CSP allows `unsafe-inline` and `unsafe-eval`** | Weakens XSS protection significantly. |
| 14 | **sessionStorage for userData** | Cached user data persists through tab lifecycle — stale subscription status possible. |
| 15 | **No email verification enforcement** | Users can access dashboard without verifying email. |

